As far as I know, no one has conjectured this. 
I believe that the first sculptures that we have - Venus of Willendorf - 35,000 years old- and the many very similar sculptures, all in this identical pose, were made by and for women. 
▫️▫️
I believe this because all of these sculptures are made from soft stone. I believe that they are fertility symbols; used to get pregnant; or prevent pregnancy; they could be carried around; played with by children; stuck in the dirt. 
▫️▫️
The pose is never mentioned: Look closely at the arms on the upper breast’s.  I believe that she is expressing milk. For her baby. Of crucial importance. 
▫️▫️
Just as we now know that about 51% of all the hand prints in caves are those of women - and therefore, obviously, about that percent of the cave paintings that we have are by women, as well; so, these first great known sculptures are by women. 
▫️▫️
That’s my story and I am sticking to it. 
As I always tell student - always pose like the figures in art and you will learn a lot. 

I have no degrees; I only know what I know from looking a lot.

Behind the scenes😁✨💃🏼 
Finding my way back to the high drive. Im back feeling the high peaks of putting in effort (in all aspects of the art), even the things I’m not good at and tasks that I find say… less fun lol. I think I’ve been stuck with a feeling that everything has to be some kind of perfection, and when you feel that it’s never good enough, you’re also never happy with the outcome and despise your input. It’s not about perfection it’s about the effort. So relieve yourself of the “perfection”, put in the effort and ride on the highs of accomplishment ✨
Happy Saturday!🤎✨

Magical🤎✨

Trial and error is part of the process, even though at times, it’s extremely frustrating 😅. As I started to get these ready, I realized the butterflies were too thin and fragile to survive through the handling before firing. Shipping was also an issue. I almost gave up until I realized the butterflies can be separated and removable on the finished works. This is actually super exciting, you’ll be able to buy separate butterfly kits to customize or just change colors depending on mood/ season or to simple match different rooms or flowers ✨If I hadn’t faced an issue, this magical solution would’ve never been born❤️‍🔥

I have this fond memory from being a child and getting those shoes I’d wanted forever for Christmas. I was equally ecstatic about opening the box and receiving an extra set of shoestrings. It was something about that little detail, the little customization, that made it a little bit more special to me. We change, seasons change, mood, style, interior, likes etc. and for some reason we never tend to let Art continue it’s life of evolving, it’s usually set in stone. I wanted to make something that never stops growing, evolving or changing, or at least given the opportunity if one so would wish. My ceramic torsos and vases all come with interchangeable butterflies, to give the works an opportunity to keep changing, just as the seasons 🍁

 Butterflies attached with a double magnetic lock and makes the piece interchangeable. Separate butterfly kits will be available in a few weeks for maximal customization 💛

What she said☝️💛 (repost @where_is_frances )

I have been MIA. I’ve been going THROUGH it, big time. I could’ve posted things to make things look “perfect”, could’ve posted the “hardship”, the thing I struggle with social media is do you pretend just for the sake of it..? Do I need to act like a “brand” or what part of the “brand” do I need to follow through on? Can’t lie so I’ve been quiet, it’s been rough lately. Im digging myself back up, back up to happiness, where I belong 😃 I have the utmost best support network of strong women (and men) around me, thank you baby Jesus for them, without them I wouldn’t be anything. I am because of them. Ay ay rolling up my sleeves and here we go again 💃🏼😆🙌

A little tbt (5 years ago) to this ombré beauty 💛✨

#art #sculpture
”Draw me like one of your French girls”✨

There is no straight line, there’s no shortcuts, there will always be ups and downs, obstacles, bad days, good days, wins and losses. It’s been real cloudy for a while but I’m seeing the sun again, and it feels amazing☀️🤌. As I was sitting on the floor working (I somehow always end up there) I was thinking of things I’ve done that made me proud of myself, not what other people judge me from but myself, and I thought “your name is in Forbes, next to some of the largest brands in the world, working with one of the largest luxury fashion houses in the world”. I came from a small town in Sweden (population of 26,000) to the U.S. with 2 suitcases and didn’t know a single person here, I’m equally proud for doing that. This is a reminder to remind yourself of the feats you’ve accomplished, and remind yourself to be proud of yourself!❤️ don’t let anyone make you feel less!!
”Draw me like one of your French girls”✨

🚫“Your post may go against our guidelines on sexual activity or nudity”
This has been a constant battle for me on social media, and I’m mostly shadow banned. Every time I start posting or being active I get my “hands slapped” lol, hence why I at times stay low key to not have my account deactivated. It saddens me, because I personally don’t see my work as being “sexual” whatsoever. My whole purpose for my work was ,and remains, to do the exact opposite, to show the female body in a nonsexual, female empowering way. I wanted the female form to be able to have a space where our beauty can be showed WITHOUT being sexual or explicit, just natural beauty. I’d love to hear your thoughts, agree/ disagree? Let’s start a conversation 
#shadowbanned #meta

🧡”Canyon, 2023”, from the new series Erosion. (Available on website).
This work is a reflection on what we all have gone through the last few years, some beautiful but trying times, that left no one unscathed, that created an erosion of experiences, yet stood strong, like a willow. Despite the lack of rain, roots grew deeper, so deep that nothing could tilt the the willow, ever again. 🧡

Not only do I get to do what I love the most for a living,I also get to meet some absolutely amazing people along the way. I had the utmost pleasure to make a belly cast for the gorgeous mama @minsuepin 🥹❤️So excited for the little new addition to their beautiful family!❤️

Burnout is real, mental health is real. I believe the last couple of years have been quite tumultuous for the most of us with lots of tensions/ instability/ uncertainty. I thrive under a little bit of stress but when things tip over that’s when it becomes damaging and creates a domino effect in all aspects of life. The more stressed I’ve gotten, the less I’ve managed to be productive and that creates even more stress and I’ve become a worse version of myself. I’ve neglected “time off”, felt guilty when I do something fun outside of work etc. Last time I went to Sweden I woke up with stroke like symptoms, luckily it was inflammation on the balance nerve that connects the ear to the brain, had to crawl to the bathroom for a week 😂We woke up from an attempted break in the same night and I think that was what triggered it, my body reached its limit on stress, stress that gradually built up over time. I haven’t felt as relaxed and calm (my old self) for a very long time as I’ve been since I came to Sweden. Im at my favorite place, a small island in the Swedish archipelago, haven’t felt this relaxed in a long long time. The other day I got sick, It went over quick but I’m convinced this is the built up stress that is being released when one finally relaxes. It’s a reminder of to take care of your mind, body, soul and mental health. There is only one you!❤️ I’m making a NYE promise to myself today (lol) to take better care of myself from now on! 🩷😂
PS! I’ve started waking up in the mornings with ideas that came to me throughout the night, that’s when I know the fog is clearing✨ DS.
